{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"923a6675-6f28-402d-8252-9e205b6f3071","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01TmoRW2ZcEEDm54phiLNjKj","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing crash dump config"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01DuYNzvN4TP49QxNtTN7DgJ","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"echo \"workspace ready\"","description":"Check workspace","initial_wait":5},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check workspace"}],"interactionId":"96f0beca-d6f7-411a-9f8b-16401c44d2c6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me think about what's needed:\n\n1. For .NET NativeAOT apps, crash dump collection requires specific environment variables\n2. They need Kubernetes pod spec changes (volume mounts, env vars, etc.)\n\nLet me provide the configuration needed:\n\nFor .NET crash dumps with NativeAOT:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - Enable mini dump generation\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` - Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - Path pattern for dump files\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` - Optional, for diagnostics\n- For NativeAOT specifically, you need `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` to point to the createdump tool since NativeAOT doesn't bundle it\n\nNow I'll create a clear example with the pod spec changes.","outputTokens":428,"requestId":"7646:34F832:198553C:1D18EBA:69FE9282"},"id":"f12e41b6-36e5-416f-b30b-1aee9ceb321d","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:49:00.971Z","parentId":"66d087a9-66c5-4ff2-b130-efa826ff78cf"}
