{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"327f9da4-0264-460b-bd0c-4e2f4b9163d2","content":"Here's what you need. NativeAOT doesn't bundle `createdump`, so you must point the runtime to it explicitly via `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`.\n\n**Environment variables** for your container:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  # Enable crash dump generation\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  # Dump type: 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"\n  # Required for NativeAOT — path to external createdump tool\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n  # Write dumps to the persistent volume with timestamp\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/dumps/coredump.%p.%t.dmp\"\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes** — add a volume + mount so dumps survive pod restarts:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      # ... existing config ...\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi  # adjust based on expected dump size\n```\n\n> For durable collection, replace `emptyDir` with a `persistentVolumeClaim` so dumps survive pod eviction/rescheduling.\n\n**Key points:**\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` is **required** for NativeAOT since there's no bundled `createdump`.\n- Dump type `4` (Full) gives the most diagnostic info but produces larger files. Use `2` (Heap) if space is tight.\n- The `%p` and `%t` tokens expand to PID and timestamp, preventing overwrites.\n- Ensure the container process has write permissions to `/dumps`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"96f0beca-d6f7-411a-9f8b-16401c44d2c6","outputTokens":487,"requestId":"7646:34F832:1986EEB:1D1ADFA:69FE928C"},"id":"c2abd944-c6da-4d0f-9128-a5921e3eecd3","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:49:11.419Z","parentId":"32180bec-82fb-4e9c-ad28-df5d030fe9fe"}
